{ The Umbrella is a technique where the attacking king shelters behind a pawn to avoid rook checks during the final push. Black plays 1...f4!, which White must capture with gxf4, placing White's own pawn on f4. Black's king then settles on f3, using the f4-pawn as an "umbrella" that blocks White's rook from delivering checks along the third rank. Without this pawn shelter, a king escorting a passed pawn would be driven away by perpetual harassment; the umbrella pawn solves this problem elegantly. }
1... f4! 2. gxf4 Rb2+ 3. Kf1 Kf3 $19 { Black use the pawn f4 like an Umbrella for protecs the black king from checks } 4. Ra1 Rh2 5. Kg1 Rg2+ 6. Kh1 Rg8 7. Kh2 e2 8. f5 Kf2 9. Kh3 Rg5! (9... e1=Q?? 10. Rxe1! Kxe1 11. Kh4! $10) *


